Edit: *snicker*<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				Northshire valley, for example &#8212; we spent an inordinate amount of time on it. Where do we put the trainers, how does the combat feel, etc. We probably spent more time on it than any other area, by an order of magnitude. After we made it fun, then we made it big. We didn&#8217;t go out and build the entire world of WoW until we knew what we were building. It didn&#8217;t make sense to do that until we had figured out all the details of the fun. If you have to retrofit the fun into the content, you&#8217;re gonna be screwed.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
